body:
@alex-mazzariol, thanks for clarifying. I am going to leave this open. We shouldn't be crashing, we should be displaying an error. If this is not a mono issue, but just an older framework in the bin directory issue, then it could happen more often.

I am mainly thinking of the scenario where people build multiple projects into the same bin directory. If some test projects have been upgraded, but not others, the framework could be any version. Of course, this is a mistake on the developers part as all dependencies for the solution should be at the same version, but ideally we wouldn't crash.

I am going to leave the confirm label on this to see if it is a more general non-Mono problem, but drop the priority to low since it is a user error and move it out to post 3.0. @CharliePoole, if you think we should look at this earlier, move it back :smile:
